Temporary traffic changes around the University of Wollongong and TAFE NSW will be in place from Monday 27 February 2023 for approximately six weeks, to minimise congestion for the start of the university year. 


The temporary traffic changes are as follows:

  • M1 southbound traffic exiting at University Avenue will be diverted left, to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout, between 7.45am and 9.15am on weekdays. 
  • Traffic at Irvine Street will be diverted to the University Western Access route via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road during peak periods.  
  • Motorists accessing the M1 northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Avenue during peak periods will be diverted via Murphys Avenue and Robsons Road.  

Bus access from University Avenue into Irvine Street will not be affected during diversions and outside peak periods traffic will continue to access the University via Irvine Street and Northfields Avenue.

Continuous closure northbound from 1130pm Sat 25 Feb to 7am Sun 5 Mar

Resident access will be maintained.
